#### location ####
text: Hill of Tara
----
lat: 53.58237
----
lon: -6.604439999999999
#### text ####
text: The Hill of Tara! Despite being a historically significant place, it was treated like a local park, with kids and dogs running around playing (and a bus full of tourists). This is where Irish kings were inaugurated, and all the lumps are ancient (neolithic/iron age) monuments, earthworks and tombs. It has an amazing view of the surrounding areas, apparently including the sea on a (rare) clear day.
#### image-collection ####
images:

##### image #####
image: eESYGitNrVTPgIFCRg4FP0TI9EM.jpg
-----
alt: TODO
-----
css_classes: 
-----
caption: 
-----
video_link: 
#### text ####
text: Like everything in Ireland, the Irish history is overlaid with Christian churches & monuments, even (especially?) at a site of such Irish importance.
#### image-collection ####
images:

##### image #####
image: TDFp90d-_0KRtct2wwEGiWDX45Y.jpg
