#### location ####
text: Newgrange
----
lat: 53.694744199999995
----
lon: -6.4826327
#### text ####
text: Next stop on the tour was Newgrange! It's very restricted access, with limited daily tickets and only small groups allowed inside at a time, and no photos. The chamber is accessed through a narrow tunnel, then opens into a vaulted chamber 5m/16ft high made of huge rocks supported by smaller rocks that have been standing untouched for 5200 years. The experience defies words.
#### image-collection ####
