#### location ####
text: Coppingers Court, Fortified House
----
lat: 51.571647899999995
----
lon: -9.066860199999999
#### text ####
text: Coppinger Court was a fortified house (not quite a castle) that burnt down in the 1600s and was left like that for the next 400 years. Excitingly, we lucked out and ran into a descendant of the Coppinger family there! The tale we heard from our guide was that the owner was involved with shady dealings, particularly loaning money with stringent terms and repossessing the house when the terms were violated. He liked this place & kept it. At some point he had to leave for business and told his son to burn the place if he wasn't back in 3 days! He was gone for more than 3 days, and came back to the place burning. The descendent was visiting from South Africa and had a very similar family tale, just with the servants instead. (Sadly, it was actually burned in the Irish rebellion of 1641, but it was a good story.)
