#### text ####
text: Next we stopped at Kilcoe Old Graveyard, an overgrown medieval church and cemetery. While the cemetery has been in use since the 1400s, all the visible gravestones were from between the 1800s and modern time. There were so many graves, the dirt inside the ruined church was visibly higher than it had been originally.
